LAGOS  – The Lagos State Government, on Thursday, announced the diversion of traffic along the Public Works Road at Ikeja for rail level crossing asphalt laying. The diversion, which com­menced early in the morning, the government explained would continue till 6.00 am on Friday, April 22, 2022. A statement by Dr. Frederic Oladeinde, the Commissioner for Transportation, Lagos State said that the diversion was in line with the Nigerian Railway Modernisation Proj­ect (Lagos-Ibadan section) with an extension to Lagos Port at Apapa. Oladeinde emphasised that the asphalting of the level crossing on the Public Works Road, Ikeja was necessary to ease traffic flow across the rail track in the section. According to the diversion plan, motorists from Govern­ment Reserved Area (GRA), are to make use of Oba Akin­jobi Way to link Airport Under Bridge to access Agege Motor Road, while those from Osho­di coming into the GRA, Ikeja would be diverted to the Air­port Bridge or Adegbola Level Crossing for their desired des­tinations. The statement added: “Road users are therefore advised to comply with the traffic direc­tions provided by the Traffic Enforcement Personnel on the ground as well as road signals to minimize inconvenienc­es during the rehabilitation works.”